ICMA Says Cyrus Ardalan Elected Chairman, Succeeds Rudloff

-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-05-27T11:13:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/icma-says-cyrus-ardalan-elected-chairman-succeeds-rudloff.html
The International Capital Market
Association  elected Cyrus Ardalan as chairman with immediate
effect, ICMA said in a  statement  today.  Ardalan, who is vice chairman of  Barclays Capital  and who
has previously worked at BNP Paribas SA, succeeds Hans-Joerg
Rudloff, who was chairman of ICMA from 2005.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in Paris at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Armstrong at 
 parmstrong10@bloomberg.net  